	   <tr><td colspan=2>Howdy, Alerithon!<br>This is how the kick in "Instill Doubt" works-- as succienctly as I can put it!&nbsp;&nbsp;:/ <br><br>Once you press the hot key for ID you must wait until you see the phrase "You are not scaring anyone" before you press your other specials.  Now, before all the other monks who have mastered this ability on their keyboards in RL write in and jump all over me, let me explain that yes, I understand that you can use a different special earlier.  Indeed, if you use a view that allows you to see your monk in the 3rd person view and you see the kick occur, THAT is when you can use your other specials (Dragon, Tiger, etc. etc.).  However, I tend to play solely in 1st person view and cannot see my kick normally, so I have to wait until I see the no-scare message. <br><br>This is the format I use:<br>1) Flying Kick (or whatever special you happen to be using)<br>2) ID<br>3) Wait for the message or observe the fear it provokes and<br>4) either re-do your special attack (Dragon, Tiger etc. etc.) or start pummeling while chasing the mob when it begins running away from you.<br>5) Keep IDing the mob even as it runs away because sometimes you are lucky and it sticks for a second time in a row (but you have to be close enough for it to take effect).<br>6) If the ID does not work start at #1 again.<br><br>"Kick" is the kick utilized in "Instill Doubt", so the higher your skill in kicking, the higher the damage you dispense to the mob.<br><br>As for the success rate it is utterly dependent on the type of mob (some are easier to fear than others), your typing skills (timing, in other words), your skill level in ID, and location.  Yes, I said location.  Once again, before other high level monks jump all over me on this, let me explain this is ENTIRELY ancedotal.  It appears to me that in dungeons (a very very bad place to ID!) "Instill Doubt" has a bit of a higher rate of success than in open spaces.  I do NOT claim that this is fact, it simply appears to me that it works better in dungeons.  I do not use ShowEQ or any other parser as that would take the fun out of the game for me.  'Nuff said on that.<br><br>I hope this makes things clearer (yeah right! clear as mud!).<br><br>--Pusbag Infection<br><br>/em Pusbag looks foolish while doing the "One Legged Stork" move he copied from the Karate Kid since he is a shammy, not a monk.<br>&nbsp;<br>Emperor and Shamanic High Priest of the Trolls<br>"Worship Innoruuk, you worthless cattle!"<br></td></tr>
